* The problem asks solution with log(m+n) which means we have to use something like a binary search to find the median of the two sorted array. Here, to simplify the question, we assume that (len(nums1)+len(nums2))%2==1, which means we only need to find the single element in either nums1 or nums2 that is the overall (m+n+1)/2 th number. 
* What we are going to do is to find the **ith** number in nums1 and **jth** number in nums2 which satisfy the **i+j=(m+n+1)/2**, and also **max(nums1[i],nums[j])<=min(nums1[i+1],nums2[j+1])**, and the median would simpley be the **max(nums1[i],num2[j])**, because we have find overall **(m+n+1)/2th** number. Assume **len(nums1)<len(nums2)**, we can start from end of nums1 with **i=len(nums1)** and **j=(m+n+1)/2-i**. Now if the pair satisfy the condition, we output the median. However if **nums1[i]>nums2[j+1],we move i to the left in a binary search fashion** and if **nums1[i+1]<num2[j],we move i to the right as in binary search.** There're some small issues you have to take care of when you are at the boundary, **i==0 or i==len(nums1)**, but the whole idea was what I explained above.
* I will show a process below of the binary search process, hopefully it will make it easier to understant.
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/dtshuai39/image_1588536549.png)

* The code is as follows, please fogive me for not writing it in a very consise way. 
